        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Play U-words defensively:</strong> Place them adjacent to premium squares you want to protect. The U ending prevents opponents from extending into those high-value positions.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>BIJOU is your best U-ender:</strong> At 14 points with the J tile, it scores well AND creates a dead end. Play it near triple-word squares for maximum strategic value.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Don't save U for Q if Q is gone:</strong> Track whether Q has been played. If it has, dump your U immediately using TOFU, TUTU, or ECRU rather than holding dead weight.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>PLATEAU/TABLEAU for bingos:</strong> These 7-letter words use all your tiles for the 50-point bonus. Keep them in mind when your rack has common letters plus U.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Learn the French borrowings:</strong> BIJOU, BAYOU, PLATEAU, TABLEAU, ECRU — French contributes most U-ending words to Scrabble. A few minutes memorising these pays off throughout your games.</span></li>
      </ul>

